54,http://www.armslist.com/posts/2940054,For Sale:  HECKLER & KOCH USP 9MM COMPACT V1,"Salem, Albany, Corvallis, Monmouth, Dallas, Salem, Oregon",$ 750,"Listed On: Wednesday, April 23, 2014",Handguns,Heckler & Koch                                                                                ,9mm Luger (9x19)                                                                                ,Double / Single Action                                                                                ,Pistol,"LNIB, less than 100 rounds fired.
Case, 2 10 round magazines and lock.
Local sale (mid Willamette Valley) cash only, current ODL.
Serious inquiries only please.
Description:

USP9 Compact V1 DA/SA 9mm. USP Compacts are smaller and lighter than large frame USPs. The reductions in trigger reach and grip circumference increases conceal ability and enhances shooting ergonomics. Unlike some subcompact semiautomatic pistols that use a difficult to shoot """"two-finger grip"""" frame, the USP Compact uses a narrow, full-hand grip frame with a choice of interchangeable extended or flush-fitting magazine floor plates. This makes the pistol easy to shoot without sacrificing conceal ability. Like their large frame predecessors, USP Compacts are designed with the demanding needs of the law enforcement and military shooters in mind. Using a modified linkless Browning-type action, the USP Compact is built to take the punishment of high-energy +P loads. To reduce the length of the slide and barrel on the USP Compact, the mechanical recoil reduction system found on large frame USPs has been replaced by a specially designed flat compression spring contained in the captive recoil spring assembly by a polymer absorber bushing. Specifications: - Corrosion proof fiber-reinforced polymer frame - Grooved target triggers - Polygonal bore profile for increased velocity, easier cleaning, and longer barrel life - Can be converted to any of nine trigger firing modes - Specially designed captive recoil spring assembly with polymer absorber bushing - One piece machined slide made from nitro-carburized steel - No snag, bobbed hammer - Flared recurve trigger guard - Universal mounting grooves for installing accessories - Ambidextrous magazine release lever - Contoured, extended slide release - Extractor doubles as a loaded chamber indicator."""

The stock is in good shape and the wood is much heavier duty than the other SKS variants (Russian, Chinese etc)The gun has a decent bore, not shiny but not pitted or rusty either. I have shot it up to 50 yards and it shoots pretty accurate.
THE ISSUES:

When I bought the rifle and tried to shoot it, it would not cycle the rounds so it was basically a bolt action rifle. I suspected a gas leak since the gas valve switch was pretty beat up and the gas tube wobbled so I purchased a brand new CNC Warrior stainless steel gas valve/switch. It helped a little bit with the cycling but still has issues and stove pipes/jams.
Also not a huge deal but the front sight ring seems to have been broken by the previous owner (see pic). It's only the brace and not the sight so it is only a cosmetic issue.

I suspect the gas tube is the culprit since it wobbles a little still. I just can't seem to find another original one available to try it out so I'm getting rid of the whole rifle. I'm letting it go for $200 cash if anyone is up to the task of making this thing run again. SKS are pretty simple in design so I don't think the problem would be too difficult to fix. I imagine the worst case scenario is you have to buy another gas cylinder. Sorry the cheap sling is not included since it's broken.
$200 cash only. Price is firm. Do not bother with lower offers as they will be ignored. I don't need to sell this gun. MUST HAVE AND SHOW PTP OR PTC TO PURCHASE.
I am available to meet in public M-F after 4:30pm or weekends after 3pm. I can only meet in the metro area, preferably around Saint Paul. I am not willing to drive to the outer suburbs due to flakes.
Thanks for looking!"
